2 9-14-601. Central bank digital currency; prohibition;
3 definitions.
4
5 (a) No state agency shall accept or require payment
6 in the form of a central bank digital currency for any
7 government service, or for the payment of any taxes or
8 fees.
9
10 (b) No state agency shall use public funds to assist
11 in any manner in the testing, adoption or implementation of
12 a central bank digital currency.
13
14 (c) As used in this article:
15
16 (i) "Central bank digital currency" means a
17 digital medium of exchange, token or monetary unit of
18 account issued directly by the United States federal
19 reserve system or any analogous federal agency;
20
21 (ii) "State agency" means the state of Wyoming
22 or any of its branches, agencies, departments, boards,
23 instrumentalities or institutions.
