1 (iv) The centralization of financial data
2 leading to increased surveillance and a loss of financial
3 privacy;
4
5 (v) The collection of data inherent to a central
6 bank digital currency providing the means for government
7 control of a person's financial activity.
8
9 (c) The legislature urges Congress to prohibit the
10 establishment of a central bank digital currency through
11 Congress's federal legislative authority.
12
13 (d) The Secretary of State shall transmit copies of
14 this section to the President of the United States, to the
15 President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of
16 Representatives of the United States Congress and to each
17 member of the Wyoming Congressional Delegation.
